      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soak the fruit, at least 2 hours",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{raisins}}, {{sultanas}}, {{mixed-peel}}, and {{blanched-almonds}} in a bowl. Pour over the {{kirsch}} if using, stir, cover, and leave for at least 2 hours (overnight is better). If not using kirsch, the fruit goes in dry.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{plain-flour}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{mixed-spice}}, and {{cardamom-green}} in a large bowl. Beat the {{eggs}} with the {{whole-milk}}, {{unsalted-butter}} for the dough, and {{vanilla-extract}}. Pour into the flour and mix to a smooth, quite stiff dough. Knead for 8 minutes until the dough comes together. Add the soaked fruit and nuts and knead until evenly distributed, the dough will seem lumpy but will smooth as you work.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "First rise, 60 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cover and leave in a warm place for 60 minutes. The enriched fruit-laden dough rises more slowly than a lean dough; expect a modest increase rather than a full double.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the marzipan",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{almond-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}} for the marzipan, and {{egg-whites}} together until a firm paste forms. Shape into a log about 20 cm long and 3 cm in diameter. If it is too sticky, chill for 10 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line a baking tray with baking paper. On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough into an oval roughly 30 × 20 cm. Place the marzipan log just off-centre along the length. Fold one half of the dough over the marzipan and press the edge down firmly to seal. This is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "stollen fold",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yiunb00008ov456m2mz8q"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Transfer to the lined tray. The loaf should have a rounded hump on one side where the marzipan sits.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Second prove, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cover loosely and leave for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 170°C fan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 40 to 45 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until the crust is deep brown and a skewer inserted into the centre (avoiding the marzipan) comes out clean. The internal temperature should read 92°C. As soon as the stollen comes out of the oven, brush it all over with the melted {{unsalted-butter}} for finishing, the hot crumb absorbs it immediately. Leave for 5 minutes, then sift the {{icing-sugar}} for finishing over the top in a thick, even layer. It should look white. Cool completely on a rack, then wrap tightly in foil.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
